- VSCode Version: 1.5.3
- OS Version: Windows 10

I have released an alpha of extension `vscode-jumpy` [(marketplace)](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=wmaurer.vscode-jumpy) [(repo)](https://github.com/wmaurer/vscode-jumpy).

The extension creates many decorators in the currently activated editor by calling `createTextEditorDecorationType` (once) and then `setDecorations` with each decoration referencing a different SVG file via `contentIconPath`.

I have noticed a slightly slow rendering performance that is perceptible to the user.

I haven't managed to be able successfully use data urls, which I would have presumed would be faster than references to files on the file system. Is this supposed to be supported, or is this planned? I would like to be able use `DecorationOptions` as follows:

```
return {
    range: new vscode.Range( ... ),
    renderOptions: {
        dark: {
            after: {
                contentIconPath: `data:image/svg+xml;utf8,<svg ... > ... </svg>`
            }
        }
    }
};
```
